description:
&lt;p&gt;An exciting opportunity has arisen for a Senior Sister / Charge Nurse in the friendly Critical Care Outreach team at the QEQM Hospital; they will be responsible for overseeing the high standards of care required for looking after the deteriorating/critically ill patients.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Post holder must be a Registered General Nurse with a degree in Nursing or working towards a degree or equivalent as well as the preparation of mentors course or equivalent. A minimum of 5 years’ experience in acute care nursing at is required.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The post holder will be expected to provide professional leadership, advice and guidance for nursing practice within the hospital and being a resource for all nursing staff.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;They will also need to have expert clinical skills, great communication skills and clinical assessment skills. They will contribute to ensuring that the Nurses within the hospital are developed to maximize their contribution to the achievement of the Trusts service goals and upholds and models the Trust values.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;NameDeirdre McFarlaneAdditional contact information&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Deirdre McFarlane&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;deirdremcfarlane@nhs.net&lt;/p&gt;
